  <span id="freeText14817256672440162851" style="display:none">What a triumph this collection is! I loved every story. Every page was absolutely golden. It has everything I could possibly want in a a short story collection. It has flawed characters, the setting is beautifully described every time, and the stories themselves leave a lasting impact. I highly urge anyone to read this collection. Vladimir Nabokov, one of my favorite authors, thought his stories were entertaining but didn't leave a lasting impression and I couldn't disagree more. Anton Chekhov was called the master of the short story for a reason.</span>
